 the binary class name for resource loading. Does it have a public default constructor and a public member class with no arguments?\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating resource dependencies**\\n\\nI’m considering whether an earlier positive use of the dependency bundle failed due to missing resources. It seems like the class bundle might work, so I need to import ListResourceBundle. I should also remove the MissingEntryException and assertThrown. I'll add a nested `public static class Messages extends ListResourceBundle`. The ResourceBundle base name will use `Messages.class.getName()`, which results in a `$` at runtime. It looks like I have a plan here!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_8b21Jkl3OsC1wFGUgWg9YC40|fc_0a1488a9184b2708016a25af2fabbc8195a60d156bf19b14b3", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.bouncycastle/bcprov-jdk18on/1.77/src/test/java/org_bouncycastle/bcprov_jdk18on/LocalizedMessageTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "import org.bouncycastle.i18n.LocalizedMessage;\nimport org.bouncycastle.i18n.MissingEntryException;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n\nimport java.util.Locale;\nimport java.util.TimeZone;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThatThrownBy;\n\npublic class LocalizedMessageTest {\n    private static final String MISSING_MESSAGES = \"org.bouncycastle.missing.Messages\";\n    private static final TimeZone UTC = TimeZone.getTimeZone(\"UTC\");\n\n    @Test\n    void reportsMissingResourceBundleWithDefaultClassLoader() throws Exception {\n        LocalizedMessage message = new LocalizedMessage(MISSING_MESSAGES, \"missingMessage\");\n\n        assertThatThrownBy(() -> message.getEntry(\"title\", Locale.ENGLISH, UTC))\n                .isInstanceOfSatisfying(MissingEntryException.class, exception -> {\n                    assertThat(exception.getResource()).isEqualTo(MISSING_MESSAGES);\n                    assertThat(exception.getKey()).isEqualTo(\"missingMessage.title\");\n                    assertThat(exception.getLocale()).isEqualTo(Locale.ENGLISH);\n                    assertThat(exception.getClassLoader()).isNull();\n                });\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void reportsMissingResourceBundleWithExplicitClassLoader() throws Exception {\n        LocalizedMessage message = new LocalizedMessage(MISSING_MESSAGES, \"missingMessage\");\n        ClassLoader resourceLoader = ClassLoader.getSystemClassLoader();\n        assertThat(resourceLoader).isNotNull();\n        message.setClassLoader(resourceLoader);\n\n        assertThatThrownBy(() -> message.getEntry(\"text\", Locale.ENGLISH, UTC))\n                .isInstanceOfSatisfying(MissingEntryException.class, exception -> {\n                    assertThat(exception.getResource()).isEqualTo(MISSING_MESSAGES);\n                    assertThat(exception.getKey()).isEqualTo(\"missingMessage.text\");\n                    assertThat(exception.getLocale()).isEqualTo(Locale.ENGLISH);\n                    assertThat(exception.getClassLoader()).isSameAs(resourceLoader);\n                });\n    }\n}\n", "newText": "import org.bouncycastle.i18n.LocalizedMessage;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n\nimport java.util.ListResourceBundle;\nimport java.util.Locale;\nimport java.util.TimeZone;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\npublic class LocalizedMessageTest {\n    private static final String TEST_MESSAGES = Messages.class.getName();\n    private static final TimeZone UTC = TimeZone.getTimeZone(\"UTC\");\n\n    @Test\n    void loadsClassBackedResourceBundleEntryWithDefaultClassLoader() throws Exception {\n        LocalizedMessage message = new LocalizedMessage(TEST_MESSAGES, \"localizedMessage\");\n\n        String title = message.getEntry(\"title\", Locale.ENGLISH, UTC);\n\n        assertThat(title).isEqualTo(\"Localized title\");\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void loadsClassBackedResourceBundleEntryWithExplicitClassLoader() throws Exception {\n        LocalizedMessage message = new LocalizedMessage(\n                TEST_MESSAGES,\n                \"localizedMessage\",\n                new Object[] { \"argument\" });\n        ClassLoader resourceLoader = ClassLoader.getSystemClassLoader();\n        assertThat(resourceLoader).isNotNull();\n        message.setClassLoader(resourceLoader);\n\n        String text = message.getEntry(\"text\", Locale.ENGLISH, UTC);\n\n        assertThat(text).isEqualTo(\"Localized text with argument\");\n    }\n\n    public static class Messages extends ListResourceBundle {\n        @Override\n        protected Object[][] getContents() {\n            return new Object[][] {\n                    { \"localizedMessage.title\", \"Localized title\" },\n                    { \"localizedMessage.text\", \"Localized text with {0}\" }\n            };\n        }\n    }\n}\n"}]}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 726, "output": 1919, "cacheRead": 47616, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 50261, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1780854547823, "responseId": "resp_0a1488a9184b2708016a25af14b5948195955da344deafa78c"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_8b21Jkl3OsC1wFGUgWg9YC40|fc_0a1488a9184b2708016a25af2fabbc8195a60d156bf19b14b3", "toolName": "edit", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Successfully replaced 1 block(s) in tests/src/org.bouncycastle/bcprov-jdk18on/1.77/src/test/java/org_bouncycastle/bcprov_jdk18on/LocalizedMessageTest.java."}], "details": {"diff": "    ...\n  6  */\n  7 package org_bouncycastle.bcprov_jdk18on;\n  8 \n  9 import org.bouncycastle.i18n.LocalizedMessage;\n-10 import org.bouncycastle.i18n.MissingEntryException;\n 11 import org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n 12 \n+12 import java.util.ListResourceBundle;\n 13 import java.util.Locale;\n 14 import java.util.TimeZone;\n 15 \n 16 import static org.